This is the program 'statistics_summary'.

/* Analyze a set of data points */
Create 'N' as an int with value 5.
Create 'data' as a double array of size 5 with values: 
    12.5, 
    15.0, 
    10.5, 
    14.2, 
    and 13.8.

Create 'avg' as a double.
Create 'std' as a double.

/* Use blessed statistical functions */
Call 'mean' with 'data' and 'N' stored to 'avg'.
Call 'standard_deviation' with 'data' and 'N' stored to 'std'.

Call 'printf' with "Mean: %.2f, StdDev: %.2f\n", 'avg', and 'std' stored to nothing.

End of the program 'statistics_summary'.
